\pard\qc\sa180\f0\fs44\b THOG2 Chebyshev Sheet\line Requirements Specification\b0\par
\pard\qc\sa220\f0\fs24\i v0.2 - integrated compact-depth, block, and semantic sheet geometry\i0\par
\pard\qc\sa320\f0\fs18 Draft requirements document - July 2026\line Target location: docs/THOG2_Chebyshev_Sheet_Requirements_Specification_v0.2.rtf\par
\pard\sa220\f0\fs22 This document consolidates the original THOG2 Chebyshev sheet requirements, the curve/sheet/block basis requirements, and the new semantic sheet requirements into one logical specification. It is organised as if the geometry ladder, clean-axis rule, block variants, and semantic sheet variants had been designed together.\par

\pard\sa180\sb260\f0\fs32\b Table of Contents\b0\par
\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs22 1. Concept and architecture\par
\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs22 2. Vocabulary, axes, and naming\par
\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs22 3. Basis families and compact orders\par
\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs22 4. Geometry base options\par
\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs22 5. Geometry presets\par
\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs22 6. Detailed geometry requirements\par
\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs22 7. Configuration and identity requirements\par
\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs22 8. Out of scope\par
\page

\pard\sa180\sb260\f0\fs32\b 1. Concept and architecture\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 1.1 Core concept\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.1.1\b0  THOG2 shall treat a repeated transformer matrix family across depth as one structured learned object, not as an unrelated list of dense layer matrices.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.1.2\b0  The compact representation shall be learned directly during training. It shall not be defined as a post-training approximation to an already trained dense model.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.1.3\b0  Depth shall be treated as the primary compact axis for THOG2 weight geometry. Other compact axes shall be admitted only when their architectural meaning is explicit.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.1.4\b0  The architecture shall preserve the ordinary GPT/nanoGPT training boundary: token IDs remain categorical, the data pipeline and next-token objective remain conventional, and the transformer topology remains recognisable.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.1.5\b0  The compact parameterisation shall define the hypothesis class. Materialisation of dense-equivalent weights, where used, is an execution boundary and not the architectural source of truth.\par

\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 1.2 Transformer matrix families\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.2.1\b0  The specification shall apply to repeated transformer matrix families: attention input projection, attention output projection, MLP expansion, and MLP contraction.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.2.2\b0  The attention input projection may be stored in packed QKV form for compatibility, but the architecture shall understand Q, K, and V as semantic roles.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.2.3\b0  The semantic attention axes are qkv_role, head, local_head_channel, d_model_input, and d_model_output.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.2.4\b0  The semantic MLP axes are hidden_channel, d_model_input, and d_model_output.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.2.5\b0  A linear weight shall be understood in the operator convention W[out_features, in_features]. Rows produce output channels; columns are input channels read by the row.\par

\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 1.3 Clean-axis rule\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.3.1\b0  A compact basis may span only axes that are meaningful enough to support ordered or basis-like interpolation.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.3.2\b0  Depth is a clean ordered axis and is always eligible for compact representation.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.3.3\b0  The residual d_model axes may be treated as compressible basis-like axes for sheet and block experiments.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.3.4\b0  MLP hidden channels, attention heads, QKV role, and local head channels may be kept whole when the experiment is intended to preserve their semantic identity.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.3.5\b0  No compact basis shall smear across QKV role or attention head index unless a later specification explicitly approves that research direction.\par

\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 1.4 Whole axes and compressed axes\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.4.1\b0  A whole axis is an explicit discrete index in the coefficient tensor. No Chebyshev or DCT smoothing is applied across that axis.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.4.2\b0  A compressed axis is represented by a finite orthogonal basis order. The learned coefficients span that axis through the selected basis family.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.4.3\b0  Each geometry option shall be describable by listing its compressed axes and its whole axes.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.4.4\b0  For two-dimensional sheet geometries, depth is one compressed sheet axis and exactly one non-depth matrix axis is the other compressed sheet axis. Remaining matrix axes stay whole.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 1.4.5\b0  For three-dimensional block geometries, depth and two matrix axes are compressed together. This is more compact but more restrictive than a sheet geometry.\par

\pard\sa180\sb260\f0\fs32\b 2. Vocabulary, axes, and naming\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 2.1 Axis vocabulary\b0\par
\pard\f1\fs17\sa120
Axis                Meaning                                                  Requirement note\line
------------------  -------------------------------------------------------  ------------------------------------------\line
depth              Layer index across the repeated transformer stack.        Usually compressed by P.\line
output_rows        Rows of W[out,in]; one row produces one output feature.   Whole in generic_sheet_col.\line
input_cols         Columns of W[out,in]; one column reads one input feature. Compressed in generic_sheet_col.\line
d_model_input      Residual-stream channel axis read by a projection.        Usually compressible.\line
d_model_output     Residual-stream channel axis produced by a projection.    Compressible in one attention-output option.\line
hidden_channel     MLP intermediate channel.                                 Whole in sheet_mlp.\line
qkv_role           Query, key, or value role.                                Always whole in semantic attention.\line
head               Attention head index.                                     Always whole in semantic attention.\line
local_head_channel Scalar channel inside one attention head.                 Whole or compressed depending on option.\par
\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 2.2 Public naming rules\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 2.2.1\b0  The name legacy_sheet_col shall remain a compatibility alias for the original sheet-column behaviour.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 2.2.2\b0  The preferred public name for that behaviour shall be generic_sheet_col.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 2.2.3\b0  The name depth shall be the preferred public name for the depth-only geometry. The older name curve may remain as a compatibility alias where needed.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 2.2.4\b0  Preset names shall be flat, short, and descriptive. User-facing commands shall not require independent selection of MLP, QKV, and attention-output components unless an advanced override mode is deliberately added.\par

\pard\sa180\sb260\f0\fs32\b 3. Basis families and compact orders\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 3.1 Basis family\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.1.1\b0  CHEBY shall mean the Chebyshev first-kind compact basis family used by THOG2.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.1.2\b0  CHEBY shall use the finite sampled, QR-stabilised basis convention unless a later version explicitly changes that convention.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.1.3\b0  DCT shall mean a real orthonormal DCT basis family. The initial DCT version shall correspond to DCT-II orthonormal basis columns.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.1.4\b0  Geometry requirements shall be independent of basis family. A geometry describes axes and coefficient layout; a basis family describes how compressed axes are evaluated.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.1.5\b0  The selected basis family and basis version shall be part of model identity.\par

\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 3.2 Compact orders\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.2.1\b0  P shall denote the retained depth order.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.2.2\b0  Q shall denote the retained generic row/column or d_model order when a single generic matrix-axis order is used.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.2.3\b0  J shall denote the retained per-head QKV/local-channel order where applicable.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.2.4\b0  O shall denote the retained attention-output local-channel order where applicable.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.2.5\b0  X shall denote the retained MLP d_model order where applicable.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.2.6\b0  Y shall denote the retained MLP hidden-channel order where applicable.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 3.2.7\b0  A geometry shall state which orders it consumes. Unused orders are configuration noise and shall not change the model identity for that geometry.\par

\page
\pard\sa180\sb260\f0\fs32\b 4. Geometry base options\b0\par
\pard\sa120\f0\fs22 This table lists the base options available to the resolver. Some are complete whole-model presets. Others are module-level components used to form presets in Section 5.\par
\pard\f1\fs16\sa160
#  Base option          Applies to              Brief description                              Compressed axes                                  Uncompressed axes\line
-- -------------------- ----------------------- ---------------------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------ ----------------------------------------------\line
1  dense                all families            Conventional dense transformer weights.        none                                             all matrix axes, all layers\line
2  depth                all families            Depth-only compact geometry; alias curve.      depth                                            output_rows, input_cols\line
3  generic_sheet_col    all families            Original sheet-column behaviour.               depth, input_cols                                output_rows\line
4  legacy_sheet_col     all families            Compatibility alias for generic_sheet_col.     depth, input_cols                                output_rows\line
5  generic_sheet_row    all families            Transposed generic sheet ablation.             depth, output_rows                               input_cols\line
6  mlp_block            MLP only                Existing MLP block geometry.                   depth, MLP output axis, MLP input axis           MLP family/direction\line
7  head_aware_block     attention only          Existing attention block; keeps role/head.     QKV: depth, local, d_model_in; out: depth, d_model_out, local   QKV: role, head; out: head\line
8  sheet_mlp            MLP only                Semantic MLP sheet.                            depth, d_model_input/output                      hidden_channel\line
9  sheet_qkv            QKV only                Semantic QKV sheet.                            depth, d_model_input                             qkv_role, head, local_head_channel\line
10 sheet_out_dmodel     attention output only   Output sheet gives Q to d_model output.        depth, d_model_output                            head, local_head_channel\line
11 sheet_out_local      attention output only   Output sheet gives Q to local channel.         depth, local_head_channel                        d_model_output, head\par

