\pard\sa180\sb260\f0\fs32\b 6. Detailed geometry requirements\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 6.1 Dense and depth\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.1.1\b0  The dense preset shall retain ordinary independently stored layer weights and shall not consume compact basis orders.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.1.2\b0  The depth geometry shall represent W_l[o,i] as a function of layer depth while leaving output_rows and input_cols explicit.\par
\pard\li360\f1\fs18\sa120 depth: W_l[o,i] = sum_p C[o,i,p] * B_depth[l,p]\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.1.3\b0  Depth shall be the primary compact baseline for comparing whether matrix-axis compression is useful beyond layerwise sharing.\par

\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 6.2 Generic sheets\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.2.1\b0  generic_sheet_col shall keep output_rows whole and compress depth with input_cols.\par
\pard\li360\f1\fs18\sa120 generic_sheet_col: W_l[o,i] = sum_pq C[o,p,q] * B_depth[l,p] * B_in[i,q]\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.2.2\b0  generic_sheet_row shall keep input_cols whole and compress depth with output_rows.\par
\pard\li360\f1\fs18\sa120 generic_sheet_row: W_l[o,i] = sum_pq C[i,p,q] * B_depth[l,p] * B_out[o,q]\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.2.3\b0  generic_sheet_row shall be treated as a geometry ablation, not as a replacement for semantic sheet design.\par

\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 6.3 Existing block geometries\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.3.1\b0  mlp_block shall apply only to MLP expansion and MLP contraction families.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.3.2\b0  mlp_block shall compress depth, MLP output axis, and MLP input axis together.\par
\pard\li360\f1\fs18\sa120 mlp_block: W_l[o,i] = sum_pqr C[p,q,r] * B_depth[l,p] * B_out[o,q] * B_in[i,r]\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.3.3\b0  head_aware_block shall apply only to attention families.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.3.4\b0  head_aware_block shall keep qkv_role and head whole. It shall not construct a compact basis over head index.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.3.5\b0  For QKV, head_aware_block shall compress depth, local head output channel, and residual-stream input channel per role and per head.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.3.6\b0  For attention output, head_aware_block shall compress depth, residual-stream output channel, and local head input channel per input head.\par

\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 6.4 Semantic MLP sheet\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.4.1\b0  sheet_mlp shall apply only to MLP expansion and MLP contraction families.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.4.2\b0  For MLP expansion, sheet_mlp shall keep hidden_channel whole and compress depth with d_model_input.\par
\pard\li360\f1\fs18\sa120 MLP up: whole = hidden_channel; compressed = depth, d_model_input\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.4.3\b0  For MLP contraction, sheet_mlp shall keep hidden_channel whole and compress depth with d_model_output.\par
\pard\li360\f1\fs18\sa120 MLP down: whole = hidden_channel; compressed = depth, d_model_output\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.4.4\b0  The purpose of sheet_mlp is to test whether MLP hidden channels should remain discrete semantic units while residual d_model axes are compressed.\par

\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 6.5 Semantic attention sheet\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.5.1\b0  sheet_qkv shall keep qkv_role, head, and local_head_channel whole.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.5.2\b0  sheet_qkv shall compress depth with d_model_input.\par
\pard\li360\f1\fs18\sa120 QKV: whole = qkv_role, head, local_head_channel; compressed = depth, d_model_input\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.5.3\b0  sheet_out_dmodel shall keep head and local_head_channel whole, and shall compress depth with d_model_output.\par
\pard\li360\f1\fs18\sa120 attn_out_dmodel: whole = head, local_head_channel; compressed = depth, d_model_output\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.5.4\b0  sheet_out_local shall keep d_model_output and head whole, and shall compress depth with local_head_channel.\par
\pard\li360\f1\fs18\sa120 attn_out_local: whole = d_model_output, head; compressed = depth, local_head_channel\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 6.5.5\b0  The attention presets shall include both attention-output choices because the correct second sheet axis for attention output is not settled by the clean-axis rule alone.\par

\pard\sa180\sb260\f0\fs32\b 7. Configuration and identity requirements\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 7.1 Resolved identity\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 7.1.1\b0  Each run shall have a requested preset and a resolved compact identity.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 7.1.2\b0  Resolved compact identity shall include model family, requested preset, MLP component, QKV component, attention-output component, basis family, basis version, model dimensions, and the compact orders consumed by that identity.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 7.1.3\b0  Aliases shall resolve deterministically. legacy_sheet_col shall resolve to generic_sheet_col. curve shall resolve to depth.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 7.1.4\b0  Run names and metadata shall be sufficient to distinguish all presets in Section 5.\par

\pard\sa120\sb180\f0\fs26\b 7.2 Component composition\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 7.2.1\b0  Internally, the resolver may use separate MLP, QKV, and attention-output component selectors.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 7.2.2\b0  The normal user-facing interface shall expose flat presets rather than requiring users to compose component selectors manually.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 7.2.3\b0  Advanced component overrides may exist for ablation work, but a preset must always expand to a complete, auditable component tuple.\par

\pard\sa180\sb260\f0\fs32\b 8. Out of scope\b0\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 8.1.1\b0  This specification does not define correctness tests, implementation staging, or performance targets.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 8.1.2\b0  This specification does not assess current experimental results.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 8.1.3\b0  This specification does not require compaction of token embeddings, positional embeddings, LayerNorm, LM head, or biases.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 8.1.4\b0  This specification does not spectralise the sequence-position axis or replace causal attention with a fixed spectral mixer.\par
\pard\sa80\f0\fs22\b 8.1.5\b0  Alternative bases beyond CHEBY and DCT, including learned bases, wavelets, and Legendre bases, remain future candidates.\par
}
